item.title: My First 10K
item.description: I ran my first 10K race today at the 2015 Panerathon in Youngstown, OH. The following describes how it went. Pro-tip: Don’t eat a full pizza AND Chipotle the night before running a race. Mile 0: Blast off to the bass drop of Calvin Harris’s Sweet Nothing Remix Mile 0 - 1: Pew, pew, pew, I keep passing people. Such slowpokes. This is fun. Clock fastest mile time at 7:34.

item.title: Skydiving
item.description: In order to cross off another thing off my Impossible List, I went skydiving today. Iâ€™m not too big on large men strapped to my back with our pelvic regions in close proximity, so I chose to go the Accelerated Free Fall (AFF) route. Start Skydiving in Middletown, OH, the number 1 dropzone in the world, offers the First Jump Course for people who want to learn the basics of skydiving and may want to pursue a license in the future.
